english:
  title: On the Appointment of Yun Eon-sik as Minister of Works
  author: Gwak Dong-soon
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I issue this edict. In seeking one to advance all my endeavors, I look among those who stand in attendance at court, and find in you one whose accumulated virtue befits my deepest desire. Thus do I issue this radiant decree, that my utmost sincerity in seeking joy together may be made manifest.

    Yun Eon-sik, Censor of the Gate and Overseer of the Three Departments, possesses a breadth of mind that is vast and remote, and conduct rooted in virtue. Through the grace of his family's standing, he came forth in service, entering the way of office in his youth. As descendant of generals and ministers renowned for their names, he bears the dignified bearing of one who practices courteous deference. His fair reputation rose early within the inner court, and his marriage ties bound him to the royal clan. When the Queen Mother established proper decorum, she strengthened the bonds of the nine kinships, and when the late king ruled through filial piety, he showed honor to the outer family. For generations he has held lofty positions and been long employed in service. As attendant in the inner palace, he never deviated from my side; as keeper of the privy council, he remained faithful day and night. Having labored through many reigns, he may truly be called a minister of old.

    Consider how your ancestors, through daily conquest of new lands, assisted in the glorious deeds of our founding. Their authority struck fear among distant peoples, and even now there is no anxiety from the east. Remembering your house's service through the ages, I grant this reward to your lineage. Year by year you have advanced, month by month been appointed, ever with increased stipend and positions of purity. In the ranks of the Eastern Hall and court attendants, you stood with dignified bearing; in the duties of the Three Departments and salt administration, you handled each matter with precision. Recognizing your past achievements and your recent accomplishments, I promote you to lead the Ministry of Works and rank you among the eight chief ministers. The proper use of the five materials and nine standards falls within your province—how could I withhold their employment in times of great drought or flood?

    Ah, the sovereign summons the worthy through reward, and the minister offers himself to the state through service. When ruler and subject thus support one another, this becomes an encounter rarely granted in this world. Merit and renown are not so difficult to achieve—you should unfold an endless glory. Do not diminish this mandate, but make it endure in beauty forever. You are hereby appointed Minister of Works, all else to remain as before.
  footnotes:
    - The 'three kinships' (九族) traditionally refers to extended family relationships across nine degrees of relation
    - The 'five materials' (五材) and 'nine standards' (九軌) are classical terms referring to the proper administration of public works and governance
